<subSubSection pageId="70" pageNumber="71" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="70.[151,1437,340,726]" pageId="70" pageNumber="71">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,345,412,438]" pageId="70" pageNumber="71">Distribution</emphasis>
. East Pacific: 
<collectingCountry box="[504,597,412,438]" name="Ecuador" pageId="70" pageNumber="71">Ecuador</collectingCountry>
(
<collectingRegion box="[611,736,412,439]" country="Ecuador" name="Galapagos" pageId="70" pageNumber="71">Galápagos</collectingRegion>
); single record from 
<collectingCountry box="[964,1053,413,439]" name="Panama" pageId="70" pageNumber="71">Panama</collectingCountry>
(Bahía Honda in 
<collectingRegion box="[1247,1352,413,439]" country="Panama" name="Veraguas" pageId="70" pageNumber="71">Veraguas</collectingRegion>
) highly doubtful (
<bibRefCitation author="Haig, J." box="[261,383,448,474]" pageId="70" pageNumber="71" pagination="1 - 440" refId="ref72816" refString="Haig, J. (1960) The Porcellanidae (Crustacea: Anomura) of the Eastern Pacific. Allan Hancock Pacific Expedition, 24, 1 - 440." type="journal article" year="1960">Haig 1960</bibRefCitation>
; see below).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="70" pageNumber="71" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph blockId="70.[151,1437,340,726]" pageId="70" pageNumber="71">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,294,485,511]" pageId="70" pageNumber="71">Ecology</emphasis>
. Intertidal and subtidal, known depth range: 
<quantity box="[810,900,485,511]" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" metricValueMax="2.0" metricValueMin="0.0" pageId="70" pageNumber="71" unit="m" value="10.0" valueMax="20.0" valueMin="0.0">0–20 m</quantity>
; under rocks, on sandy bottoms and associated with corals (
<bibRefCitation author="Haig, J." box="[290,412,520,546]" pageId="70" pageNumber="71" pagination="1 - 440" refId="ref72816" refString="Haig, J. (1960) The Porcellanidae (Crustacea: Anomura) of the Eastern Pacific. Allan Hancock Pacific Expedition, 24, 1 - 440." type="journal article" year="1960">Haig 1960</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Hickman, C. P. &amp; Zimmerman, T. L." box="[423,768,520,547]" pageId="70" pageNumber="71" refId="ref73387" refString="Hickman, C. P. &amp; Zimmerman, T. L. (2000) A field guide to crustaceans of Galapagos: an illustrated guidebook to the common barnacles, shrimps, lobsters and crabs of the Galapagos Islands. Sugar Spring Press, Lexington, 156 pp." type="book" year="2000">Hickman &amp; Zimmerman 2000</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="70" pageNumber="71" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="70.[151,1437,340,726]" pageId="70" pageNumber="71">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,308,557,583]" pageId="70" pageNumber="71">Remarks</emphasis>
. With the exception of 
<specimenCount box="[567,746,556,582]" pageId="70" pageNumber="71" type="generic">three specimens</specimenCount>
collected in Bahía Honda, 
<collectingCountry box="[1047,1139,557,583]" name="Panama" pageId="70" pageNumber="71">Panama</collectingCountry>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Sivertsen" authorityYear="1933" box="[1148,1329,556,582]" class="Malacostraca" family="Porcellanidae" genus="Petrolisthes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="70" pageNumber="71" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="brachycarpus">
<emphasis box="[1148,1329,556,582]" italics="true" pageId="70" pageNumber="71">P. brachycarpus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is known only from the Galápagos Archipelago (
<bibRefCitation author="Haig, J." box="[595,719,592,619]" pageId="70" pageNumber="71" pagination="1 - 440" refId="ref72816" refString="Haig, J. (1960) The Porcellanidae (Crustacea: Anomura) of the Eastern Pacific. Allan Hancock Pacific Expedition, 24, 1 - 440." type="journal article" year="1960">Haig 1960</bibRefCitation>
). 
<bibRefCitation author="Haig, J." box="[740,877,592,619]" pageId="70" pageNumber="71" pagination="1 - 440" refId="ref72816" refString="Haig, J. (1960) The Porcellanidae (Crustacea: Anomura) of the Eastern Pacific. Allan Hancock Pacific Expedition, 24, 1 - 440." type="journal article" year="1960">Haig (1960)</bibRefCitation>
considered the material of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Sivertsen" authorityYear="1933" box="[1190,1373,592,618]" class="Malacostraca" family="Porcellanidae" genus="Petrolisthes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="70" pageNumber="71" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="brachycarpus">
<emphasis box="[1190,1373,592,618]" italics="true" pageId="70" pageNumber="71">P. brachycarpus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from Bahía Honda as “extralimital”, probably due either to an accidental introduction or (perhaps more likely) to an error in the label accompanying these specimens. Therefore, the presence of this species in 
<collectingCountry box="[1130,1219,665,691]" name="Panama" pageId="70" pageNumber="71">Panama</collectingCountry>
requires confirmation.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
